  "texts": [
    "But since (a ′, b ′) ⊆ O, (a, b) ∩ (a ′, b ′) ̸ = ∅ contradicts (a, b) ∩ O = ∅ from above.",
    "Thus, σ ̸ ⊆ σ O, which completes the proof.Next, we define a relation that only relates sets of pairs to regular open sets:• σR ◁ O iff ∀(a, b) ⊆ O ∃⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ: (a, b) ⊆ (a ′, b ′).",
    "Note that since each O is a union of open intervals, σR ◁ O implies that O ⊆ ⟨a,b⟩∈σ (a, b).Clearly R ◁ satisfies up-R and R-down.",
    "For R-refinability +, givenσR ◁ O, let O ′ = (a, b) for one of the (a, b) ⊆ O.",
    "Then σR ◁ O implies that there is an ⟨a ′, b ′ ⟩ ∈ σ such that O ′ ⊆ (a ′, b ′)."
  ]
}